<p>Rich snippets increase <a href="/glossary/click-through-rate/">click-through rates</a> by 58% compared to standard search results. Yet fewer than 35% of websites have any structured data at all.</p>
<p>That means most businesses hand free clicks to competitors who took 30 minutes to add <a href="/glossary/schema-markup/">schema markup</a>.</p>
<p>Rich snippets are the enhanced search results that display star ratings, prices, FAQ dropdowns, event dates, and other visual elements directly in Google. They pull this data from structured markup in your page's HTML. No markup means no rich snippets.</p>
<p>This guide walks you through the exact 7-step process to earn rich snippets for your site. We have published 3,500+ blogs across 70+ industries, and every article includes structured data that qualifies for <a href="/glossary/rich-results/">rich results</a>.</p>
<p>Here is what you will learn:</p>
<ul>
<li>The difference between rich snippets, featured snippets, and SERP features</li>
<li>Which schema types Google still supports in 2026 (and which ones it dropped)</li>
<li>How to write JSON-LD markup for the 6 most valuable rich result types</li>
<li>How to test, deploy, and monitor your structured data</li>
<li>Common mistakes that prevent rich snippets from appearing</li>
</ul>
